Reasoning: The paper deals with model checking problems for enriched Mu-calculi, which are formal logics used for specifying and verifying properties of computer systems. The paper uses automata-theoretic approaches to solve these problems, which is a common technique in the field of formal verification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Other likely sub-categories include cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), cs.LM (Logic in Computer Science), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
